---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="Programs - Nischal Khanal">
	<div class="container">
		<h1>Programs</h1>
        <p><a href={base}>Home</a></p>
		<hr />

		<div class="section">
			<h3>Operating System: Arch Linux</h3>
			<p>
				I use Arch Linux as my daily driver. It's minimal, lightweight, and gives me
				full control over my system.
			</p>

			<h3>Window Manager: DWM</h3>
			<p>
				DWM (Dynamic Window Manager) is my window manager of choice. I've customized
				it to fit my workflow perfectly.
			</p>

			<h3>Text Editor: Neovim</h3>
			<p>
				Neovim is where I spend most of my time coding. With a few plugins, it
				becomes a powerful IDE.
			</p>

			<h3>Terminal: Alacritty</h3>
			<p>
				Alacritty is a GPU-accelerated terminal emulator. It's fast, simple, and
				works great with my setup.
			</p>

			<h3>Browser: Brave</h3>
			<p>
				Brave is my primary browser. It blocks ads and trackers by default, keeping
				my browsing private and fast.
			</p>

            <h3>File Manager: Ranger and Dolphin</h3>
            <p>I use Ranger for terminal navigation and Dolphin for a user-friendly graphical interface.</p>

            <h3>Music/Video Player: VLC </h3>
            <p>VLC supports nearly every media format, making it my go-to player.</p>

            <h3>Torrent Client: Transmission</h3>
            <p>Transmission is lightweight and straightforward, making file downloads easy to manage.</p>

            <h3>Document Writing: Google Docs and LibreOffice</h3>
            <p>I use Google Docs for collaboration and LibreOffice for offline document creation.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
